You plan to hire other specialty physical therapists or provide other underrepresented services, such as pool therapy or massage. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bd/Start-a-Physical-Therapy-Business-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Start-a-Physical-Therapy-Business-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bd/Start-a-Physical-Therapy-Business-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Start-a-Physical-Therapy-Business-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
